Maybe a bit late to the party, but you could also read as a string and then parse it:

    LocalDate date = LocalDate.parse(data.get (&quot;ngDate&quot;).asText()); 

This will work if the date is ISO_LOCAL_DATE formatted, otherwise:

    DateTimeFormatter formatter = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(&quot;d-MMM-yyyy&quot;);
    LocalDate date = LocalDate.parse(data.get(&quot;ngDate&quot;).asText(), formatter);

Here the argument of `DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern` can be any date formatting pattern. In the example it will parse date strings of the type &quot;1-Aug-2009&quot;.

